cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper proposes a novel framework for improving Deep Reinforcement Learning algorithms by enabling temporal abstractions in the action space. The paper focuses on improving the performance of three different policy search algorithms in different domains, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of Atari 2600 and Mujoco domains suggests that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the use of Deep Deterministic Policy Gradients in the TORCS car racing domain suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
